<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="117" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1437,1157,2007]" pageId="16" pageNumber="117">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,1157,1182]" pageId="16" pageNumber="117">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Anterior dorsum with pattern similar to that of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Fabricius" baseAuthorityYear="1794" box="[815,920,1157,1181]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Apogonalia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="histrio">
<emphasis box="[815,920,1157,1181]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="117">A. histrio</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, without orange areas. Pronotum with pair of anterolateral dark brown maculae adjacent to eyes. Forewing pinkish with brown stripes on veins; clavus with yellow stripe adjacent to claval sulcus; costal area with yellow stripe; two transverse blackish stripes apically. Face yellow with dark brown marks. Frons with median, inverted V-shaped dark brown mark; pair of mediolateral elongate Y-shaped dark brown marks connected to median mark; lateral margin with dark brown stripe. Clypeus with median dark brown stripe. Paraphyses with basal sclerite asymmetrical (
<bibRefCitation author="Young" box="[1043,1309,1337,1362]" pageId="16" pageNumber="117" refString="Young, D. A. (1977) Taxonomic study of the Cicadellinae (Homoptera: Cicadellidae). Part 2. New World Cicadellini and the genus Cicadella. Technical Bulletin of the North Carolina Agricultural Experiment Station, 239, 1 - 1135." type="journal article" year="1977" yearSuffix="h">Young 1977, fig. 758h</bibRefCitation>
). Aedeagal shaft with pair of ventral processes transversely aligned in lateral view (
<bibRefCitation author="Young" box="[991,1136,1374,1398]" pageId="16" pageNumber="117" refString="Young, D. A. (1977) Taxonomic study of the Cicadellinae (Homoptera: Cicadellidae). Part 2. New World Cicadellini and the genus Cicadella. Technical Bulletin of the North Carolina Agricultural Experiment Station, 239, 1 - 1135." type="journal article" year="1977">Young 1977</bibRefCitation>
, figs 758p, 759f). Female sternite VII with conspicuous central dark brown macula. Sternite VIII (
<figureCitation box="[970,1053,1409,1434]" captionStart="FIGURES 75 – 84" captionStartId="17.[151,264,1583,1606]" captionTargetBox="[152,1416,203,1557]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[151,1436,193,1563]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURES 75 – 84. (75 – 77) Apogonalia pennata Nielson &amp; Godoy, 1995, female: 75, dorsal habitus; 76, sternite VII, ventral view; 77, sternite VIII, dorsal view. (78 – 82) A. pinguis Young, 1977, female: 78, dorsal habitus; 79, left forewing, lateral view; 80, sternite VII, ventral view; 81, sternite VIII, dorsal view; 82, pygofer, lateral view. (83 – 84) A. robusta (Walker, 1851), female: 83, sternite VIII, dorsal view; 84, pygofer, lateral view. Scale bars in mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1035600/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="117">Fig. 83</figureCitation>
) with semilunar sclerotized plate, slightly concave anteromedially and truncate posteriorly. Female pygofer (
<figureCitation box="[1002,1086,1445,1470]" captionStart="FIGURES 75 – 84" captionStartId="17.[151,264,1583,1606]" captionTargetBox="[152,1416,203,1557]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[151,1436,193,1563]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURES 75 – 84. (75 – 77) Apogonalia pennata Nielson &amp; Godoy, 1995, female: 75, dorsal habitus; 76, sternite VII, ventral view; 77, sternite VIII, dorsal view. (78 – 82) A. pinguis Young, 1977, female: 78, dorsal habitus; 79, left forewing, lateral view; 80, sternite VII, ventral view; 81, sternite VIII, dorsal view; 82, pygofer, lateral view. (83 – 84) A. robusta (Walker, 1851), female: 83, sternite VIII, dorsal view; 84, pygofer, lateral view. Scale bars in mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1035600/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="117">Fig. 84</figureCitation>
) with apical, narrowly convex small lobe, ventrally delimited by slight concavity.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1437,1157,2007]" box="[199,597,1517,1542]" pageId="16" pageNumber="117">
Female length. 6.0– 
<quantity box="[423,507,1517,1542]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.1" pageId="16" pageNumber="117" unit="mm" value="6.1">6.1 mm</quantity>
(n = 3).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="117" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1437,1157,2007]" pageId="16" pageNumber="117">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,584,1553,1578]" pageId="16" pageNumber="117">Description of female genitalia.</emphasis>
Sternite VII similar to that of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Young" authorityYear="1977" box="[954,1072,1554,1577]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Apogonalia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pinguis">
<emphasis box="[954,1072,1554,1577]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="117">A. pinguis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; posterior margin with median concavity slightly narrower. Sternite VIII (
<figureCitation box="[655,743,1589,1614]" captionStart="FIGURES 75 – 84" captionStartId="17.[151,264,1583,1606]" captionTargetBox="[152,1416,203,1557]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[151,1436,193,1563]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURES 75 – 84. (75 – 77) Apogonalia pennata Nielson &amp; Godoy, 1995, female: 75, dorsal habitus; 76, sternite VII, ventral view; 77, sternite VIII, dorsal view. (78 – 82) A. pinguis Young, 1977, female: 78, dorsal habitus; 79, left forewing, lateral view; 80, sternite VII, ventral view; 81, sternite VIII, dorsal view; 82, pygofer, lateral view. (83 – 84) A. robusta (Walker, 1851), female: 83, sternite VIII, dorsal view; 84, pygofer, lateral view. Scale bars in mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1035600/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="117">Fig. 83</figureCitation>
), in dorsal view, with semilunar sclerotized plate; anterior margin of plate slightly concave medially; posterior margin truncate medially. Pygofer (
<figureCitation box="[1142,1224,1625,1650]" captionStart="FIGURES 75 – 84" captionStartId="17.[151,264,1583,1606]" captionTargetBox="[152,1416,203,1557]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[151,1436,193,1563]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURES 75 – 84. (75 – 77) Apogonalia pennata Nielson &amp; Godoy, 1995, female: 75, dorsal habitus; 76, sternite VII, ventral view; 77, sternite VIII, dorsal view. (78 – 82) A. pinguis Young, 1977, female: 78, dorsal habitus; 79, left forewing, lateral view; 80, sternite VII, ventral view; 81, sternite VIII, dorsal view; 82, pygofer, lateral view. (83 – 84) A. robusta (Walker, 1851), female: 83, sternite VIII, dorsal view; 84, pygofer, lateral view. Scale bars in mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1035600/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="117">Fig. 84</figureCitation>
) slightly produced posteriorly; posterior margin, in lateral view, with small apical lobe narrowly convex, delimited ventrally by slight concavity; disc with dorsal oblique row of long sparse macrosetae, extending from central portion to posterodorsal portion, which has both long and short macrosetae, posteroventral area with narrow oblique stripe of both long or short sparse macrosetae, extending from central portion of discal surface to preapical portion. Valvula I, in ventral view, with short lateral prominence on basal portion; basal margin broadly convex with small median emargination; blade similar to that of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Freytag" authorityYear="2004" box="[576,697,1842,1865]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Apogonalia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="angusta">
<emphasis box="[576,697,1842,1865]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="117">A. angusta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Valvula II similar to that of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Freytag" authorityYear="2004" box="[1025,1146,1842,1865]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Apogonalia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="angusta">
<emphasis box="[1025,1146,1842,1865]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="117">A. angusta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; teeth, on median portion of blade, very prominent, 1.5 to 2 times longer than high, spaced from one another about twice tooth length; preapical prominence approximately aligned to anteapical tooth.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
